definition.value:
VKP-Norway uses vkp-careplan-category to identify the different kinds of care plans.  

Examples: 
tiltaksplan
tjeneste
arbeidsplan

Example:
~~~
"category": [
   {
      "coding": [
      {
         "system":"http://ehelse.no/fhir/CodeSystem/vkp-careplan-category-v06",
         "code":"1",
         "display":"behandlingsplan"
         }
      ]
   }
]
~~~

vkp-Patient is expected. Identifier should be nathional id number of the patient.

Identifies the patient or group whose intended care is described by the plan.

Example:
~~~
 "subject":{
        "identifier":{
            "system":"urn:oid:2.16.578.1.12.4.1.4.1",
            "value":"05073500186"
        },
        "display":"Ærlend Sørgård"
    },
~~~

Identifies the individual(s) or ogranization who is responsible for the content of the care plan.

Example:
~~~
"author": [
        {
            "identifier":{
                "system":"urn:oid:2.16.578.1.12.4.1.2",
                "value":"102287"
            },
            "display":"Sykepleietjeneste, pleie- og omsorg"
        }
    ]
~~~

A simple summary of a planned activity suitable for a general care plan system (e.g. form driven) that doesn't know about specific resources such as procedure etc.

VKP-Norway uses this information to describe the contents of a CarePlan (aktivitetsplan, tjeneste or tiltaksplan). 

Example of information in a tiltaksplan:
~~~
"detail":{
   "extension": [
   {
      "url":"http://ehelse.no/fhir/StructureDefinition/vkp-detailheader-v05",
      "valueString":"Mål"
   }
   ],
      "status":"in-progress",
      "description":"27.02.2018: Trygghet ved utendørs aktivitet Reg: 27.02.2018 Aaltvedt, Vigdis (AALV) Ikke godkjent"
}
~~~
